2.21	The_Orange_Book	The Orange Book: Reclaiming Liberalism	The Orange Book: Reclaiming Liberalism is a book written by a group of prominent British Liberal Democrat politicians and edited by David Laws and Paul Marshall in 2004. Beside Laws and Marshall, the contributors include Vincent Cable, Nick Clegg, Edward Davey, Chris Huhne, Susan Kramer, Mark Oaten and Steve Webb.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/1/1d/Orange_Book.jpg/200px-Orange_Book.jpg
